    "created_at": "2015-09-09T14:12:13Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-09-09T14:12:13Z",
    "body": "> For the cache directory, you should probably set userCache instead of cache.\n\nSorry I didn't mention it in my original post, but I had also tried to set the `userCache` to a different folder and it had the same issue (new folder created, but not used). I did not think that the application was using the `userCache` because a folder named `Cache` is created with all the Electron cache, and from the documentation I would have expected a different folder name if this was the `userCache`.\n\n> `userCache` The directory for placing your app's caches, by default it is the cache directory appended with your app's name\n\nIs there a simple way to trigger a normal temporary file (that does not use the File System API) to be created to check it is working correctly?\n"
  },
