    "created_at": "2015-09-10T02:15:53Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-09-10T02:15:53Z",
    "body": "> Sorry I didn't mention it in my original post, but I had also tried to set the userCache to a different folder and it had the same issue (new folder created, but not used).\n\nIt is probably the same bug with #2668, but I'm not sure, Chrome seems to store all browser cache into hard-coded paths under `userData` and only uses `userCache` for other kinds of caches. I'll look into it in future.\n\n> Is there a simple way to trigger a normal temporary file (that does not use the File System API) to be created to check it is working correctly?\n\nIt is a hint to Chrome's internal functions, there is no guarantee that all Chrome APIs will use it.\n"
  },
